  "original_title": "\u0dc1\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd3 \u0dbd\u0db1\u0dca\u0d9a\u0db1\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dda\u0da7\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dab\u0dd3\u0db8\u0da7 \u0dad\u0dd2\u0db6\u0dda",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lankan catering for sale",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Mr. Nimal Siripalada Silva, Minister of Ports and Civil Aviation, says that the Minister of Ports and Civil Aviation, Mr. Nimal Siripalada Silva, is calling for ambitions to award 49 percent of Sri Lankan Catering Company's shares and its administration and 49 percent of airport operations and its administration to a promoter.",
        "\"Currently, Sri Lankan Catering Company is profiting to some extent. We will keep 49% of Sri Lankan Catering Company and its management, 51% for us and its management or if any investor requests more, more or more shares according to the demand of those investors at that time. Give and get some amount of money from it.",
        "When we get that amount of money, we will be able to pay off the 80 million dollars that we have mortgaged the shares of that company and another amount of money and another debt.",
        "Then the debt burden of SriLankan Airlines will be reduced to one. Next, we are creating a separate company for our ground handling. Given the related work and buildings, movable and immovable properties of that company, from there we get an income of about 5,000 million per year. Therefore, we think that we will be able to get a lot of money in restructuring it.",
        "No one comes even after giving 49% shares. Therefore, the administration should be given. We hope to call for tenders for that. We don't expect money to be used for other works from this. Pay the debt of SriLankan Airlines and get rid of the debt as much as possible.\""
      ],
